# Shell-Befehle in Windows-PowerShell-Umgebungen

ctx:Shell = `powershell`
=> !CMD- oder Unix/Bash-Befehle.

## Regeln

- Dedizierte Tools (Read, Write, StrReplace, Glob, Grep)
  > Shell-Tool für Dateioperationen.
- Shell nötig => vollständige PowerShell-Cmdlet-Namen;
  => !Aliase (`dir`, `ls`, `cat`, `rm`, `cp`, `mv`).

## Nicht-offensichtliche Muster

| Verboten | Stattdessen |
|----------|-------------|
| `mkdir -p path` | `New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path "path"` |
| `find . -name "*.php"` | `Get-ChildItem -Recurse -Filter "*.php"` / Glob |
| `export VAR=value` | `$env:VAR = "value"` |
| `echo $VAR` | `$env:VAR` |
| `head -n 10 file` | `Get-Content "file" -Head 10` |
| `tail -n 10 file` | `Get-Content "file" -Tail 10` |
| `cmd1 && cmd2` (PS < 7) | `cmd1; if ($LASTEXITCODE -eq 0) { cmd2 }` |
| `cmd > /dev/null` | `cmd > $null` |
| `cmd 2>/dev/null` | `cmd 2>$null` |
| `touch file` | `New-Item "file" -ItemType File -Force` |
